<%- include('partials/header') %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/double-trouble-in-love.css">
<nav class="navbar" id="navbar">
        <div class="navbar-container">
            <a href="#" class="nav-logo">DOUBLE TROUBLE</a>
            <ul class="nav-links">
                <li><a href="#story">Story</a></li>
                <li><a href="#characters">Characters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#chapters">Chapters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#quotes">Quotes</a></li>
                <li><a href="#journey">Journey</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <header class="hero-section">
        <div class="hero-grid">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-title-container">
                    <h1>DOUBLE TROUBLE</h1>
                    <span class="highlight">In Love</span>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-author">Deva Harsha V</div>
                <p class="hero-tagline">"The stars do not lie. This boy's life will always be caught between two paths, two hearts."</p>
                <p class="hero-hook">An ancient prophecy dictates that Arjun is destined to marry two women. Escaping his overprotective "Sister Army" and navigating the chaotic engineering campus life, he finds himself trapped between two fiercely brilliant hearts. When a hilarious family prank blurs into raw, deep reality, fate demands its ultimate due.</p>
                <a href="#story" class="hero-cta">Explore The Story</a>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-cover-wrapper">
                <div class="book-poster">
                    <img src="https://cdn-gcs.inkitt.com/vertical_storycovers/4b4663894774221a63abb184c150b664.jpg" alt="Double Trouble... In Love Book Poster">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="scroll-indicator">
            <span>Scroll</span>
            <div class="scroll-indicator-line"></div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <section class="section" id="story">
        <span class="section-label">The Synopsis</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">About The Book</h2>
        <div class="story-grid">
            <div class="story-left">
                <blockquote class="story-main-quote">
                    "This boy will grow to marry two women in his lifetime. It is written. No one—neither man nor god—can stop what has been decreed by fate."
                </blockquote>
                <div class="story-synopsis">
                    <p>During his naming ceremony, a revered old village priest foresees an extraordinary and scandalous destiny for the newborn Arjun Raghav: he will marry two women. Dismissed as superstition by his family, Arjun grows up with a playful charm, monitored closely by his legendary "Didi Sena"—a self-appointed WhatsApp sister committee determined to shield him from heartbreak.</p>
                    <p>As engineering college unfolds, fate begins weaving its complex net. Arjun is drawn to Meera, a bold, beautifully unscripted junior hiding a vulnerable past. To protect him from "trouble," his sisters initiate "Project Fake Girlfriend," pushing his fiercely confident childhood acquaintance Anjali into a public charade. But as fake fights spark into real tears, both women stand resolute, refusing to let go of the man they love.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="story-meta-panel">
                <div class="theme-container">
                    <h3>Core Motifs</h3>
                    <div class="theme-tags">
                        <span class="theme-tag">Romantic Comedy</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Destiny &amp; Stars</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">College Chaos</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Sisterly Interferences</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Emotional Dualism</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">10</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Chapters</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">1</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Main Narrator</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">2 Years</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Story Timespan</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-number">Rom-Com</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Genre</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="characters">
        <span class="section-label">The Players</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Cast of Hearts</h2>
        <div class="characters-grid">
            <div class="character-card main-role">
                <span class="char-role-badge">Protagonist</span>
                <h3 class="char-name">Arjun Raghav</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">A third-year mechanical engineering student blessed with magnetic boyish charm and restless energy, who continuously finds himself a magnet for chaos and conflicting paths of the heart.</p>
                <span class="char-traits-label">Traits</span>
                <div class="char-traits">
                    <span class="char-trait">Charming</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Calm</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Confused</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card main-role">
                <span class="char-role-badge">The Wildfire</span>
                <h3 class="char-name">Meera</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">A first-year department junior who lives boldly and speaks her unfiltered mind. Behind her cheerful exterior lies a heavy family past and an unwavering, genuine devotion to Arjun.</p>
                <span class="char-traits-label">Traits</span>
                <div class="char-traits">
                    <span class="char-trait">Vibrant</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Bold</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Loyal</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card main-role">
                <span class="char-role-badge">The Tempest</span>
                <h3 class="char-name">Anjali</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">A final-year college senior with a sharp tongue that could cut steel. Recruited by Arjun's sisters for a prank, her tough-girl shield completely shatters as she permanently falls in love for real.</p>
                <span class="char-traits-label">Traits</span>
                <div class="char-traits">
                    <span class="char-trait">Fierce</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Sarcastic</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Proud</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card supporting-role">
                <span class="char-role-badge">The Overlord</span>
                <h3 class="char-name">Radhika</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">The bossy, commanding final-year MBA cousin who acts as the supreme Prime Minister of the household and heads the protective "No-Girlfriend WhatsApp Committee."</p>
                <span class="char-traits-label">Traits</span>
                <div class="char-traits">
                    <span class="char-trait">Commanding</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Protective</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Strategic</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card supporting-role">
                <span class="char-role-badge">The Oracle</span>
                <h3 class="char-name">Pandit Vishwanath</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">An old family priest of intense reputation and sharp gaze whose uncanny astrology charts foresee inescapable cosmic patterns long before they happen.</p>
                <span class="char-traits-label">Traits</span>
                <div class="char-traits">
                    <span class="char-trait">Grave</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Mystic</span>
                    <span class="char-trait">Unyielding</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="chapters">
        <span class="section-label">The Chronicles</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Story Blueprint</h2>
        <div class="chapters-grid">
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 1</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Prophecy</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">A newborn naming ceremony changes forever when a legendary priest foresees that Arjun will marry two women in his lifetime.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 2</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Broken Heart, 10 Sisters</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Recovering from high school heartbreak, Arjun finds his college movements militaristically tracked by his fierce "Sister Army."</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 3</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Girl in the Snap</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">An Instagram notification introduces Meera, a bold junior whose electric presence pulls Arjun completely out of his protective shell.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 4</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Enter Anjali: The Fake Girlfriend</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">The sisters unleash a dangerous counter-strategy in the canteen, but the fake theater begins altering real heartbeats.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 5</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Sparks of Rivalry</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">The annual cultural fest forces Meera, Anjali, and Arjun into the same dance group, escalating tension into public stage comedy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 6</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Cracks in the Game</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Meera shares her painful past during a campus trip, pushing Arjun to an emotional breaking point where he confronts the battlefield.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 7</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Confessions &amp; Complications</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Meera states her love cleanly while Arjun overhears a devastating secret that unveils the true string-pullers behind his life.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 8</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Truth Unfolds</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">In a dramatic confrontation, masks are shed completely. Both women confess raw, unshaded truths just as an ominous guest knocks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 9</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">The Prophecy Returns</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">The old village priest returns to the campus as gossip fires ignite, forcing Arjun to stop running from his celestial destiny.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 10</span>
                <h3 class="chapter-title">Double Wedding &amp; Destiny's Cycle</h3>
                <p class="chapter-teaser">Two identical side-by-side mandaps house a wild, beautiful wedding, but fate saves its most amazing twist for the epilogue.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="quotes">
        <span class="section-label">Dialogue &amp; Prose</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Echoes from the Pages</h2>
        <div class="quotes-container">
            <div class="featured-quote-card">
                <p class="featured-quote-text">"Science is like flirting. A little boldness, a little patience."</p>
                <span class="featured-quote-author">— Meera, Chapter 3</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quotes-subgrid">
                <div class="quote-small-card">
                    <p class="quote-small-text">"Beta, if you want to cry, cry. But cry with a full stomach. No girl is worth starving for."</p>
                    <span class="quote-small-context">— Sita Raghav, Chapter 2</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-small-card">
                    <p class="quote-small-text">"Why is my love life a group project I never signed up for?"</p>
                    <span class="quote-small-context">— Arjun, Chapter 2</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-small-card">
                    <p class="quote-small-text">"Somewhere between the fake smiles and staged arguments, her heart had started betraying her."</p>
                    <span class="quote-small-context">— Narrative Prose, Chapter 7</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-small-card">
                    <p class="quote-small-text">"Remember, destiny is not always a burden. Sometimes, it is the greatest gift."</p>
                    <span class="quote-small-context">— Pandit Vishwanath, Chapter 9</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="journey">
        <span class="section-label">The Chronicle Lines</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The Path of Destiny</h2>
        <div class="timeline-container">
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">The Birth Decree</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Cradle Prophecy</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">During an idyllic village naming ceremony smelling of jasmine and sandalwood, Pandit Vishwanath sets an indelible trajectory by mapping a dual romantic fate onto baby Arjun.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">The Sister Defense</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Militarized Canteen</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">After a devastating high school heartbreak with Priya, Arjun enters engineering college flanked by a ten-sister "Didi Sena" protective WhatsApp cartel that systematically scares off prospects.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">The First True Spark</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">Terrace Epiphanies</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">Meera enters Arjun's life via a bold social media tag. Under starlight near the hostel water tank, they look past campus rumors and share their first profound, unvarnished connection.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">The Orchestrated Chaos</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Fake Announcement</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">Panicked by Meera's presence, the sisters deploy final-year senior Anjali to stage an outrageous public girlfriend performance in the crowded college canteen, triggering real jealousy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">The Melting Protection</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">The Broken Whiteboards</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">Arjun discovers his family manipulated Anjali's introduction. He confronts the architecture of the prank, causing both Anjali's sarcastic armor and Meera's fears to collide into absolute transparency.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <span class="timeline-stage">The Twin Mandaps</span>
                    <h3 class="timeline-title">Destiny's Infinite Loop</h3>
                    <p class="timeline-desc">Embracing his complex road, Arjun accepts a chaotic double wedding with both Meera and Anjali. Two years later, history repeats itself flawlessly as the nursery ward welcomes newborn twin sons under the identical star line.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section ending-section">
        <div class="ending-wrapper">
            <p class="ending-quote">"Two women, one heart — bound not by choice but by fate."</p>
            <p class="ending-message">Arjun's story closes not with a choice of elimination, but with an architectural expansion of love. Stepping away from ordinary binary expectations, the chaotic narrative transforms comedy into cosmic layout, settling into a vibrant, peaceful ecosystem where love doesn't split—it simply doubles.</p>
            <p class="ending-reflection">The camera of life pulls back as the screens fade to black, leaving behind a profound truth: some destinies are too wide to fit a single path, and true love handles chaos with a smile.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-title">DOUBLE TROUBLE... IN LOVE</div>
        <div class="footer-author">Deva Harsha V</div>
        <div class="footer-divider"></div>
        <p class="footer-quote">"Love is messy. Love is complicated. But when it's true... even fate cannot stop it."</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const navbar = document.getElementById('navbar');
            
            // Scroll fade effect for sticky navbar
            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                if (window.scrollY > 50) {
                    navbar.style.backgroundColor = 'rgba(253, 251, 247, 0.95)';
                    navbar.style.boxShadow = '0 4px 12px rgba(42, 36, 33, 0.05)';
                } else {
                    navbar.style.backgroundColor = 'rgba(253, 251, 247, 0.85)';
                    navbar.style.boxShadow = 'none';
                }
            });

            // Smooth scrolling highlighting current nav section
            const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a');
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section, header');

            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                let current = '';
                sections.forEach(section => {
                    const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                    const sectionHeight = section.clientHeight;
                    if (window.scrollY >= (sectionTop - 160)) {
                        current = section.getAttribute('id');
                    }
                });

                navLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.style.color = 'var(--text-dark)';
                    if (link.getAttribute('href').slice(1) === current) {
                        link.style.color = 'var(--primary-rose)';
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>